<br>
Our only planned raid schedule for each month is:<br>
one raid every week on Thursday<br>
one friday and one saturday raid a month - typically on The 3rd weekend in month but not a religious rule.<br>
<br>
As there is no raid council as yet raids have been posted by whatever player felt like posting them.<br>
<br>
The rules for Thursday raids are tweaked to play just their way - EVERY allied guild has free access to have any member lock up raid based on what they want.  The catch:<br>
- they can have only one raid pending per player<br>
- they can have only one raid per thursday per level range. (can't raid Hole the same day someone has planned a UP raid - but you can have lowbies raid CC that same day)<br>
- AND, you call the raid - YOU LEAD IT!<br>
<br>
Based on Loarind's guidance, it looks like the new and improved raid council will be.<br>
Drannor - Epic/raid<br>
Meeras - Epic/Raid<br>
Serano - Alliance Raids<br>
<br>
This does not mean that we are the only raid leaders - means that unless the council is increased ( I would like to include a plate class melee into the council as well, Loar) all future TF only raids will be called by we happy few.  Of course we will take into account all suggestions.   <br>
<br>
I see Drannor doing some great work on looking at various players epics.  That knowledge will become invaluble in planning our epic raids to finish off the epics in progress.  We have a few players that are very close and a couple that have yet to start.  Constant feedback to Drannor/ Meeras on your epic status will assist them in desiding when and where the best next target will be.<br>
<br>
And as we get our Confederation greesed up - we might as well get them into the mix for our epics and to accomplish their epics as well.  We might very well see an alliance Epic council form up - with prolly Drannor as our rep.  Once our alliance is formed - we will likely see the members fall into whatever virginia plan we get rolling<br>
<br>
I envision us starting to use Tuesday quest night as a good designated time to put together some of our epic raids.<br>
<br>
We will have to deside as a guild or as officers (Loar's call) if we want to extend our Scheduled Raid days or keep them as they are.  At least the framework for our combine raids is in place.  Don't know the other guilds raid schedules at all so far.  Currently it seems they raid when scheduled or with us - but haven't seen a cycle in RDoF or Torture.  It might be right in front of me but I haven't found it in any regular format on their boards ( Yes I know Aboo and Bigm are going to read this /wave ).  <br>
<br>
So how those guilds regular raids fit into ours is yet too be seen.  This brings up Guild raids vs alliance raids.  In order to clear up any confusion that may occur on this issue I recomend the following terms to the alliance charter makers and our present allies:<br>
<br>
- obviously all Thursday raids are THE night to have joint raids<br>
<br>
- If you want to invite the other guilds to your raids - please xpost your raids on each of our raid / alliance forums.<br>
<br>
- If you would prefer to keep ANY particular raid as a guild only raid - simply don't xpost it to the other guilds boards and we will get the none to subtle message! (work for you pens?)  If any player trys to invite himself to your guild only raid either gratiously accept their offer or slam the door in their face - no hard feelings either way - deal?<br>
<br>
- AND - I would expect EVERY Epic raid - regardless of day/ time to be OPEN to all of the small ally network we have established.  As always no raids are mandatory - but joint participation makes incredible things available to us.  I don't expect we would ever have a problem with any of our player base helping on an epic raid.... Just be durn carefull if you bring ANY - ANY - I repeat ANY pick up players invited.<br>
<br>
Serano the Verbose <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/upensfan62.showPublicProfile?language=EN>pensfan62</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Dead Guy</span><br>  Posts: 390<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/18/02 3:54:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftribalfury31319frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tribalfury.com/images/necro.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: raid planning</span><hr size=1> I don't like the idea of having every single day taken up by a planed event. It seems that is the way we are headed. Having one or two nights a week for &quot;planed&quot; raids is ok but when we start to fill up the calendar then where does that leave us time for other things?<br>
